...a duck egg. Blue in colour,  it was boiled and eaten. Everyone agreed how nice it was. Then Rob pointed out that tree on boats were not that uncommon, since without them there would be nothing to hold the sails up. Then, with a bowel-trembling thump, another ship fired its canon at the crew of the good ship Castlemaine. Fortuneately, everyone was in fact on the good ship Fourecks, which was some distance away, and, by incredible coincidnce, in another universe. But the faeries were worried for a moment. "Was it just coincidence? Was it planned? who knows?" And so saying,...